    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-06-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="239"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                <head>239. National Security Action Memorandum No. 54<note n="0" type="source"
                        xml:id="d239fn0">Source: <persName corresp="#p_KJF2">Kennedy</persName>
                        Library, Presidentʼs Office Files, Countries Series, Cuba—Security, 1961.
                        Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-06-26">June 26, 1961</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Service of Cuban Volunteers in U.S. Armed Forces</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has noted and concurred in your proposed program to enable Cuban
                    volunteers to serve in the U.S. armed forces, as stated in the attachment to
                    your memorandum of June 8, 1961.<note n="1" xml:id="d239fn1">
                        <ref target="#d227">Document 227</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>It is assumed that you will inform the Departments of State, Justice and Health,
                    Education and Welfare, and the U.S. Information Agency of the part each will
                    play in carrying out this program.</p>
                <pb facs="0647" n="615" xml:id="pg_615"/>
                <p>It is requested that after a suitable interval has elapsed the Department of
                    Defense prepare a report on the results of this program for transmittal to the
                    President through this office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMG2">
                            <hi rend="strong">McGeorge Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d239fn2">Printed from a copy that indicates <persName
                                corresp="#p_BMG2">Bundy</persName> signed the original.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
